@startuml
!include ../../style.puml

participant "Driver" as Driver
participant "Process" as Process
participant "MessageBus" as Bus
participant "Network" as Network

note over Driver
Can be a main() method
or a test harness
that drives the tick loop
end note

/note over Process
Responsibilities
--
onTick: advance timeouts / waiting logic
onMessage: handle message
update local state
emit messages
end note

/note over Bus
Responsibilities
--
register process handlers
send messages to network
route delivered messages
invoke handlers
handle self-messages
end note

/note over Network
Responsibilities
--
register dispatcher
queue messages
delay or drop messages
deliver on tick()
end note

== Initialization ==
Driver -> Process : create
Process -> Bus : register handler
Bus -> Network : register dispatcher

== main driver loop ==
loop while (simulation not done)
Driver -> Process : tick()
Driver -> Network : tick()
end loop


== Runtime behavior on each tick() ==
Process -> Process : advance timeouts / waiting logic
Process -> Bus : send(message)
Bus -> Network : send(message)
Network -> Network: queue(message)
Network -> Network: sendQueuedMessages()
Network -> Network: receiveMessages()
Network -> Bus : dispatch(message)
Bus -> Process : route to handler
Process -> Process : handle message

@enduml
